        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 7 at 5:19PM PDT by NWS Spokane WA</headline>
        <description>At 518 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 17
miles south of Mullan, or 17 miles south of Wallace, moving northeast
at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Avery.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
